Author: KomodoWorld#8282
Content: "hackers breached StatCounter, a popular web analytics platform. StatCounter is used by websites to gather statistics on their visitors. Websites do this by inserting a StatCounter code into their web pages. One of StatCounter's users and the main target of the attack is cryptocurrency exchange, Gate.io. The hackers that breached StatCounter inserted malicious code into platform's script. On Gate.io, this malicious code secretly replaces a user's bitcoin withdrawal address to one controlled by the hackers"
